  "notes": "Primary source RFEG club page (id=297) provided per-hole par, hcp (stroke index) and meters for Blancas, Amarillas and Rojas, plus Vc/Vs ratings. mScorecard.com independently confirms all 18 per-hole distances for White/Yellow/Red tees and all pars exactly (mScorecard lists no SI; SI taken from RFEG, same allocation across tees). Internal checks pass: pars sum to 71 (34 out / 37 in), SIs are a permutation of 1-18, tee distances sum exactly to published totals (5231/5141/4425). Rojas is rated for both genders on RFEG (men Vc 64.0/Vs 109; women Vc 67.8/Vs 119); Blancas and Amarillas are rated for men only. RFEG also lists a separate short 'Verdes' recorrido (par 58, 2310 m, women Vc 55.4/Vs 68, men Vc 53.2/Vs 62) which is a different pitch-and-putt style circuit, not a tee of the main 18-hole course, so it is excluded. Note: some aggregator sites (golfshake) show older/imperial figures (e.g. yellow 5107 yards, slope 122) that predate the current RFEG rating."
